title: I Am Jane Doe
description: This intense documentary follows real cases of American girls enslaved in the child sex trade through ads in a newspaper's online classified section.

title: I Called Him Morgan
description: Decades after serving a prison sentence for killing jazz musician Lee Morgan, his common-law wife, Helen, reflects on their lives and his legacy.

title: I'll Have What Phil's Having
description: Besides being the creator of "Everybody Loves Raymond," Phil Rosenthal also happens to be a foodie. Follow his culinary exploits around the globe.

title: I'll Sleep When I'm Dead
description: Superstar DJ Steve Aoki reflects on the driving force behind his career: his ambitious father, Benihana founder and perennial daredevil Rocky Aoki.

title: Imba Means Sing
description: Experience the hopes, dreams and challenges of three Ugandan children who travel around the world with the African Children's Choir.

title: In Defense of Food
description: Journalist Michael Pollan examines the industrially driven Western diet to show how it has ruined our health, then offers solutions for the future.

title: In Search of Israeli Cuisine
description: Restaurateur Michael Solomonov meets with Israeli cooks, vintners and writers to understand the country’s cuisine and its cultural complexities.

title: Incorruptible
description: In the streets of Senegal, a youth movement rises up against a regime bent on retaining power in this chronicle of the nation's stormy 2012 elections.

title: Inequality for All
description: Former U.S. Labor Secretary Robert Reich makes a compelling case about the serious crisis the U.S. faces due to the widening economic gap.

title: Inside Jaguar
description: A classic car enthusiast follows the painstaking process to recreate one of the world’s most exclusive cars: the Jaguar Lightweight E-Type.

title: Inside Russia's Toughest Prisons
description: Three Russian prisons unlock their doors to an international film crew and reveal what life inside is like for the nation's most brutal criminals.

title: Inside the Hunt for the Boston Bomber
description: The gripping inside story behind the terrorist bombings at the 2013 Boston Marathon involves a widespread investigation -- and an intense manhunt.

title: Inside the Mob's Bloody Valentine
description: Johnny Fratto, son of Al Capone associate Louis Fratto, deconstructs the most famous mob murder in Chicago's history with help from local experts.

title: Inside: Medical Marijuana
description: This documentary examines the world of legal marijuana and analyzes the science behind the medical properties of the world's most-used illicit drug.

title: Interview with a Serial Killer
description: In this jailhouse interview, Arthur Shawcross, the Genesee River Killer, shares candid details of his crimes and his surprising family bonds.

title: Into the Inferno
description: With stunning views of eruptions and lava flows, Werner Herzog captures the raw power of volcanoes and their ties to indigenous spiritual practices.

title: ISIS: Women Unveiled
description: Undercover reporters infiltrate a circle of female Islamic State supporters as they try to recruit British women and girls to join their ranks.

title: It's Not Yet Dark
description: A strong-willed Irish filmmaker impaired by ALS syndrome directs his first feature film, with eye-gaze technology as his only means of communication.
